ying your first fantasy cricket game:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Choose a match you would like to play</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Create your team of 11 players</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Choose your captain and vice-captain</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Enter a contest of your choice by choosing and monetary value</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Follow the match and track your progress on the leaderboard</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Fantasy Cricket Winning Tips and Tricks</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Winning at fantasy games requires skill, patience and persistence. A fantasy player gets some points based on his selection of players and their respective performance in the real matches. This is applicable across all gaming variants; be it practice contests or cash leagues.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Secondly, there are a certain number of payable positions in a league. Please note that you would be eligible to win a prize only if you fall in that bracket. It is thus that we recommend you plan your Practice Contests on a daily basis so that you can learn and evolve through the game like a pro.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Don’t play all games- Play those games that you have researched and have a decent amount of knowledge on.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Invest smartly- Don’t put all your money into one game. Divide your investments into parts (Example: You have 2000 rupees to spend in a month for Gamezy, then don’t invest more than 200 rupees per game. More games mean more chances to win).</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Never join a league before 30- 40 minutes of the deadline. Try to join before 13- 15 hours from the deadline. This process will let you plan for contingencies, like injuries or sudden squad changes.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Play 2- 4 member leagues with 1 team. And don’t play a grand league or above 10 member league with a single team.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>In maximum games, try to make an all-rounder as your captain and a premium batsman or bowler as vice-captain.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>For heavy investment, a person must choose 2- 3 member league where your opposition will not take risks &amp; choose the team carefully because of heavy investment. As fewer money leagues have more chances of losing because fewer money opponents won’t be scared to take the risk on wildcard players.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Try to stick only Head- 2- Head games, 3 or 4 member contests as the chances of winning is high &amp; competition is very low.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Before playing, do complete research on the probable playing 11, weather report, ground conditions, pitch report, player’s stats for that ground and opposition &amp; previous match performances of a player.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Do not invest more initially, first play small leagues or leagues with less entry fee, once you win an amount more than 1000 with that small investment, use it to enter into higher requirement leagues.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Don’t create teams based on youtube videos or apps, trust your knowledge and do some research regarding forms of teams and players.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Use your own instincts, and think differently, you can make 6 teams per account, which means you have 12 teams at least with two accounts. It will create more chances of winning.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Try to search for low-level competitors according to the credit score or Captain and Vice-captain that you have chosen.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Many times it so happens that if a player plays well in one match it is very likely that he doesn’t perform in the next match. If a player didn’t play well in one match, he’s likely to get end up with runs</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Always try to save up on buying all-rounders for your team, the more marquee the better. Look at players like Shane Watson, Hardik Pandya or Ben Stokes. They will bowl their maximum quota of overs and they bat consistently as well.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Do play domestic leagues from other countries and learn more about those players.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>In International matches, try to give more preferences to the players from the home team.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->', 'FANTASY CRICKET', 'Fantasy Cricket is an online system based game where you need to make a virtual team of genuine cricketers playing in genuine matches all over the world.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '94-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-05-10 14:12:42', '2023-05-10 14:12:42', '', 94, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=97', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
